Lecture 4: Social Responsibility & Corporate Citizenship. Social responsibility is an ethical framework which suggests that an entity, be it an organization or individual, has an obligation to act for the benefit of society at large. Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) is a self-regulating business model that helps a company be socially accountable to itself, its stakeholders, and the public. Key areas of CSR include environmental sustainability, ethical labor practices, philanthropic giving, and volunteering.